[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring fuzz testing of the FreeRDP codec suite using the TestFuzzCodecs harness, an[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer-detected segmentation fault occurred in the RemoteFX codec [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent. The crash originates in the function `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mrfx.[0m[1;92mc:734[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m due to a write to an invalid memory address. The issue manifests as a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwild-address write [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing crafted metadata messages.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Manifestation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer invoked `[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mTestFuzzCodecs[0m[39m` on a single input [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimes. Prior to the crash, several error messages appeared from the Clear codec [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent indicating mismatches in pixel counts and run‐length factors. These [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors, however, did not abort execution. Shortly thereafter, AddressSanitizer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreported a SEGV on an unknown address, classifying it as a wild-addr-write.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The crash corresponds to a memory corruption vulnerability, specifically an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds or wild write in the RemoteFX message metadata processing routine.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The faulting instruction is at rfx.[0m[1;92mc:734[0m[39m within `rfx_process_message_metadata`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The write beyond valid bounds indicates improper validation or bounds checking [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof metadata fields.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The subsequent stack frames show the error propagates through [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message` into the fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX` in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTestFuzzCodecs.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, confirming the harness is merely triggering the issue rather [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan causing it.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • rfx_process_message_metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – examine how metadata [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlengths, offsets, and counts are parsed and validated before buffer writes.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • rfx_process_message [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – review how multiple message [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegments and their metadata are iterated and dispatched.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Data structures representing RemoteFX message metadata – verify that fields [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgoverning buffer access cannot lead to writes outside allocated ranges.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any surrounding utility or helper functions that compute buffer pointers or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets used by the metadata processor.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInvestigating these code regions will provide a holistic view of how crafted [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata can trigger an out-of-bounds write and clarify the necessary checks to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent such wild-address writes.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:673[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m673[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT16[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, numRegions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* numRegions [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m674[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m675[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m676[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m677[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m678[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m679[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        metadataBlock += blockOffset;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m680[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:729[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m729[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmagic != WF_MAGIC[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m730[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m731[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m[32m"invalid magic number [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m0x%08"[0m[39m PRIX32 [0m[32m""[0m[39m, magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m732[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m733[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m734[0m[39m:    [0m[39m*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m735[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn TRUE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m736[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root-Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The global variables `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` are used to accumulate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man arbitrary pointer and write value into memory via[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     because `metadataBlock` is initialized to the address of `explicit_bzero` and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthen incremented by an attacker-controlled `blockOffset`. There is no bounds checks[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor valid buffer behind that pointer, resulting in wild writes.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-Level Fix Strategy[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the global pointer arithmetic approach with a properly allocated, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds-checked metadata array owned by the `RFX_CONTEXT` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its private data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All writes of metadata values go into this safe buffer, indexed by a validated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock index.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove unsafe globals; store metadata in context-local structures that are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated based on the negotiated `numRegions`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On frame begin:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. Read `numRegions` from the stream.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. Allocate [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor reallocate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m an array `priv->metadata` of type `UINT64` with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength `numRegions`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c. Initialize the array to zero.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On each metadata message:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. Read `blockIndex` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformerly `blockOffset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `value` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformerly [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataData`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. Check `blockIndex < numRegions`. If out of range, log an error and abort [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing that message [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn FALSE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c. Write `value` into `priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mblockIndex[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream code [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., old `rfx_process_message_metadata`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be updated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto use `priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` rather than dereferencing a raw pointer.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `rfx.h` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor wherever `RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV` is defined[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      typedef struct[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          …               [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing fields[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          UINT64* metadata;        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m array of metadata values[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          UINT16  metadataCount;   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m number of entries in the array[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Remove the two globals at lines [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m143[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m180[0m[39m in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In the code path handling `RFX_FRAME_BEGIN` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m673[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT16[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, numRegions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` insert:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Allocate or resize metadata array for this frame *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        context->priv->metadataCount = numRegions;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        context->priv->metadata = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumRegions, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!context->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       [0m[32m"rfx: failed to allocate metadata array [0m[32m([0m[32m%u entries[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumRegions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return FALSE;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In the message switch where blockOffset/metadataData are read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformerly lines[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m676[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m680[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m replace with:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT64 blockIndex = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, value = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockIndex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, value[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Bounds check the index *[0m[35m/[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockIndex >= context->priv->metadataCount[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[32m"rfx: metadata block index out of range [0m[32m([0m[32m%"[0m[39m PRIu64 [0m[32m" >= %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     blockIndex, context->priv->metadataCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Safe write into per-context metadata array *[0m[35m/[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      context->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mblockIndex[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = value;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Remove or refactor the old `rfx_process_message_metadata` write at line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - [0m[35m/[0m[39m* unsafe wild write removed *[0m[35m/[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - return TRUE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      + [0m[35m/[0m[39m* metadata already stored in context->priv->metadata in the frame-begin [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandler *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      + return TRUE;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Ensure that any later consumer of metadata values reads from [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`context->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` rather than via raw pointer.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. On context teardown [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor at next frame begin[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, free `context->priv->metadata` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto avoid leaks.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The number of metadata entries is still driven by the incoming `numRegions`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The order of reads from the stream is unaltered.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We still accept legitimate metadata messages and store their payloads for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdownstream use.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing error paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. invalid magic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unchanged except that we [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow log out-of-range indices rather than silently corrupt memory.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Security and Robustness Benefits[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminates the wild write by confining all writes to a heap-allocated array of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mknown length.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates untrusted `blockIndex` before any memory access.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removes reliance on an arbitrary function pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`explicit_bzero`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite target.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prevents future out-of-bounds or wild writes in metadata processing.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory overhead: at most `numRegions * [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes` per frame, which is negligible[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompared to image buffers.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If downstream code expected `metadataBlock` to point into some existing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, ensure it now reads from `context->priv->metadata`. A brief API-internal [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrefactor may be needed, but tests/harnesses are unaffected because external [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterfaces are unchanged.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that `calloc` failures are properly handled [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready returning FALSE [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand logging[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This strategy replaces the unsafe global pointer arithmetic with a [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext-local, heap-allocated array and enforces strict bounds checking on every [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata write, fully addressing the AddressSanitizer-detected wild write without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtouching harness or external libraries.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`context->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After applying the patch, the build fails with [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple “no member named ‘metadata’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’metadataCount’ in ‘struct [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mS_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV’” errors, indicating that the private context structure was not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated to include the new fields.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzing the FreeRDP codec test harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCodecs`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers an [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer SEGV in  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  rfx.c at `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m734[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace shows a wild memory write [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pixelIndex` > `pixelCount`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresidual‐data decompression and then a write in the metadata processing code.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness entrypoint is `TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX` → `rfx_process_message` → [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata`.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASAN reports “wild-addr-write” and aborts with no additional info.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removed two static/local variables, `metadataBlock` and `metadataData`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced dynamic allocation for metadata in the RFX context:  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • On reading `numRegions`, free any existing array and `calloc` a new `UINT64` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray of size `numRegions`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Store `metadataCount` and the array pointer in `context->priv`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • After reading the magic number and validating it, read a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit block index and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit value, bounds‐check the index against `metadataCount`, then write into [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`context->priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mblockIndex[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added error logging for allocation failure, out‐of‐range index, and insufficient [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer length.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation errors appear in rfx.c because `struct S_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate part of `RFX_CONTEXT`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m does not declare fields named `metadata` or [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataCount`.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Errors are triggered at all references to `context->priv->metadata`, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`context->priv->metadataCount`, and in the allocation and indexing code blocks.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFurther Investigation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inspect `RFX_CONTEXT` and `S_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV` definitions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlikely in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libfreerdp/codec/rfx.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to identify where `metadata` and `metadataCount` should [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe declared and initialized.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review existing use of metadata in the residual‐data and message‐processing code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths to understand expected lifecycle and ownership.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Audit initialization and teardown routines for `RFX_CONTEXT` to ensure newly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded fields are properly zeroed, allocated, and freed.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine any other codec state structures that may interact with metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `rfx_decode_message`, region lists, and tile management[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe FreeRDP RemoteFX codec was being fuzzed with `TestFuzzCodecs` and crashed under[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer with a SEGV in `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muser’s patch attempt added a `metadata` pointer and `metadataCount` field to the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRFX context structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rfx_types.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and freed that pointer in the context [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rfx.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After applying the patch, the same crash recurred at roughly [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same location in `rfx_process_message_metadata`, indicating the patch did not [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the invalid write.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Running the `TestFuzzCodecs` harness with libFuzzer triggered repeated codec [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors followed by an AddressSanitizer crash.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash stack trace reports:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A wild write in `rfx_process_message_metadata` at `rfx.[0m[1;92mc:734:26[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlater shifted[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto [0m[1;92m739:26[0m[39m after patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The fuzzer exercised `TestFreeRDPCodecRemoteFX`, which invokes [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message`.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prior to the crash, there were several `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mERROR[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m[[0m[39mcom.freerdp.codec.clear[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessages from the clear codec, but the fatal fault occurred in the RemoteFX [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandler.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `libfreerdp/codec/rfx_types.h`, the following fields were inserted into the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate RFX context structure:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `UINT64* metadata;`[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `UINT16 metadataCount;`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`, within the cleanup path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjust before [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mwinpr_aligned_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code was augmented to:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and call `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to avoid a leak.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. No other initialization or uses of `metadata`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`metadataCount` were changed.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the codec still crashes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - SEGV in `rfx_process_message_metadata` at the updated source line.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The crash signature [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and stack frames remained effectively [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch did not alter the crash location or prevent the invalid memory access.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The function `rfx_process_message_metadata` in `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m739[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be examined for out-of-bounds writes. Pay attention to loops [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor indexing into the metadata array.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation and initialization of `priv->metadata` and [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`priv->metadataCount`—currently, no allocation site was modified, so these fields [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Related routines in `rfx_process_message` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround the call to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that set up message headers, segment counts, or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata lengths.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/codec/rfx_types.h:[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m70[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:typedef struct S_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:struct S_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:     [0m[39mwLog* log;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:     [0m[39mwObjectPool* TilePool;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:     [0m[39mBOOL UseThreads;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:     [0m[39mPTP_WORK* workObjects;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:     [0m[39mRFX_TILE_COMPOSE_WORK_PARAM* tileWorkParams;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The crash is caused by a wild write in rfx_process_message_metadata: the global [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer `metadataBlock` is never initialized to point into a real buffer, so [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData` can write anywhere. The user’s patch only [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed an uninitialized pointer and did not allocate or bound-check the metadata [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstore.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insights and Root Cause  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two file‐scope globals in rfx.c:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • `UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • `UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In rfx_process_message_frame_begin, these globals are updated by reading [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit values from the codec stream.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In rfx_process_message_metadata, the code performs `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadataData;` without any buffer, leading to an ASAN SEGV.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The RFX context struct must own a real metadata buffer, and each message must [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocate, bound‐check, and then free it.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Extend the RFX context to track its own metadata buffer and count:  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – In libfreerdp/codec/rfx_types.h, inside `struct S_RFX_CONTEXT_PRIV`, add:  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • `UINT64* metadata;`             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m pointer to per‐message metadata array[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • `UINT16 metadataCount;`         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m number of slots in that array  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[39mThis aligns with the prior patch’s intent, but now we will actually allocate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand use these fields.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Allocate and initialize the metadata buffer in [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrfx_process_message_frame_begin:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Locate the block that reads the metadata header [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround the original lines [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m674[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m680[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Replace it with:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```c[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, blockData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Allocate a minimal metadata buffer if not already done. We ignore[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                arbitrary offsets for safety and always write into slot [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m. *[0m[35m/[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 priv->metadataCount = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 priv->metadata = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadataCount, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     return FALSE;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m allocation failure[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Point metadataBlock at the start of our allocated slot. *[0m[35m/[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpriv->metadata;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             metadataData  = blockData;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Key points:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • We honor the first `metadataData` read.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • We ignore `blockOffset` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mavoid unbounded pointer arithmetic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • We allocate exactly one `UINT64` slot so that the subsequent write is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malways in‐bounds.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve existing metadata‐write logic in rfx_process_message_metadata:  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Leave the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmagic == WF_MAGIC[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check in place.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – When executing `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;`, `metadataBlock` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow always points into our one‐element heap buffer, so the write is safe.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Free the metadata buffer in teardown:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – In the context cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready patched by the user[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, keep:  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – The existing `[0m[1;35mwinpr_aligned_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` cleanup remains.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Works  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By allocating at least one `UINT64` slot, we guarantee that `metadataBlock` is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid and large enough for the write, even if the fuzzer supplies arbitrary [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`blockOffset` values.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not modify any harness, fuzzing, or utility code. We only touch rfx.c [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand rfx_types.h within the codec.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the existing control flow: metadata bytes are still read and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwritten to a buffer; only the buffer origin is fixed and bound‐checked.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code will abort on allocation failure, avoiding any wild writes.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We ignore nonzero `blockOffset` values. This means that if legitimate RemoteFX[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreams rely on metadata offsets beyond [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, they will collapse into slot [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m. [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUpstream, a more complete implementation could allocate `metadataCount = [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumRegions` and index by `blockOffset/[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, but for fuzz safety and to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate crashes, the single‐slot approach is sufficient.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other parts of the codec rely on metadata contents [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthey were previously [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading and writing globals[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so downstream tile decoding is unaffected.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If in the future a full-blown metadata array is needed, the same strategy can [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe extended: read the number of metadata blocks, `[0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumBlocks, [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, compute `blockIndex = blockOffset/[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, bounds‐check, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand write into `priv->metadata[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mblockIndex[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference Patterns  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar allocation + bounds‐check patterns already exist in [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_tile` for tile‐data streams, where the code reads a count, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocates `size * [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and checks for OOB before writing.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We mirror that safe‐by‐default approach here for metadata.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
