[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing run of the FreeRDP RemoteFX codec [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCodecs`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered an [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer SEGV in `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. To [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the invalid write into metadata storage, a patch was proposed that adds a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadata` array and `metadataCount` field to the codec’s private context [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`S_RFX_CONTEXT`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, allocates the array when first needed, and frees it on teardown.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the patch fails to compile: within `rfx_process_message_metadata` the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier `priv` is undefined, leading to six “use of undeclared identifier [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m‘priv’” errors.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer command: `TestFuzzCodecs -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During processing of a malformed RemoteFX frame, several clear‐codec errors [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprint [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pixelIndex … != pixelCount …`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then AddressSanitizer reports:  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ERROR: AddressSanitizer: SEGV on unknown address … [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpc …[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     The signal is caused by a WRITE memory access.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     SCARINESS: [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-write[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x562e2b631fc5[0m[39m in rfx_process_message_metadata [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/codec/[0m[95mrfx.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m734:26[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: SEGV [0m[35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/codec/[0m[95mrfx.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m734:26[0m[39m in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrfx_process_message_metadata[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash indicates that `rfx_process_message_metadata` writes to an invalid [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor uninitialized pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`metadataBlock`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when parsing [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit metadata blocks.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `rfx_types.h`, two new members were added to `struct S_RFX_CONTEXT`:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     UINT64* metadata;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     UINT16  metadataCount;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the context teardown path [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rfx_context_free`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `priv->metadata` is freed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif non‐NULL.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `rfx_process_message_metadata` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m673[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after reading [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`blockOffset` and `blockData`, code was inserted to:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Allocate `priv->metadata` on first use [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `calloc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, setting [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataCount = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Redirect `metadataBlock` to point at `priv->metadata`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Store `blockData` into the allocated slot.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Full snippet from patch:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         priv->metadataCount = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         priv->metadata = [0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpriv->metadataCount, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return FALSE;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m priv->metadata;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     metadataData  = blockData;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation errors in `rfx.c`:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     error: use of undeclared identifier [0m[32m'priv'[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!priv->metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           ^~~~[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     error: use of undeclared identifier [0m[32m'priv'[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       priv->metadataCount = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           ^~~~[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All errors stem from `priv` not being declared in the scope of [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata`.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Further Investigation  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To fully address both the crash and the compilation failures, the following [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mareas should be examined:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The beginning of `rfx_process_message_metadata` to see how the context and its[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate data are referenced [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. whether a `priv` alias is available or if [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`context->priv` must be used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definitions and usages of `metadataBlock` and `metadataData` variables: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtheir types, scopes, and how they feed into subsequent decoding routines.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The lifecycle of `S_RFX_CONTEXT` and `S_RFX_MESSAGE` to ensure metadata [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstorage is correctly sized, tracked [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`metadataCount`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and freed exactly once.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other codec routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rfx_process_message`, any buffer pool or frame‐handling[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that consume metadata, to verify matching expectations [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. multiple [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata blocks, indexing logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consistency between header declarations [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rfx_types.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and source usage in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx.c` to prevent mismatches or undeclared identifiers.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
